  <static seed="1110" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/FractionArithmetic/DivideFractions10.pg">
    <statement><p>Divide: <m>\displaystyle{ \frac{5}{7} \div \frac{7}{4} }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="9" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{20}{49}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>When we do division with fractions, as with</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\frac{5}{7} \div \frac{7}{4} }</m></p>
<p>we first change division to multiplication, and at the same time flip the second fraction. In this case, we have</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\frac{5}{7} \cdot \frac{4}{7} }</m></p>
<p>Then we do fraction multiplication as usual. The full process is:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}[t]
    \frac{5}{7} \div \frac{7}{4}
        \amp = \frac{5}{7} \cdot \frac{4}{7} \\
        \amp = \frac{5 \cdot 4}{7 \cdot 7} \\
        \amp = \frac{20}{49}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
